During his podium interview with Eddie Jordan, Vettel said: 'It's been a while I've not been on the top step, and my first time with Scuderia Ferrari. There was a big change over the winter, and the welcome the team gave me when I arrived was fantastic.

'I've only done two races, but I'm so proud of today. We beat them (Mercedes) fair and square, I guess that's why it's a bit emotional. This is a great achievement and we have a great car.

'Today was a very, very special day, and will remain a part of me. Thank you to the team - grazie Italia. I want to celebrate today and get p****d tonight.'

